{{for|the administrative subdivision|Baft County}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name = Baft |native_name = بافت |settlement_type = City |image_skyline = |imagesize = 150px |image_caption = |pushpin_map =Iran |mapsize =150px |subdivision_type = [[List of countries|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Iran|Province]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Kerman Province|Kerman]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Counties of Iran|County]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Baft County|Baft]] |subdivision_type3 = [[Bakhsh]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Central District (Baft County)|Central]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = 1328 |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2016 Census |population_total =34,517 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref> |population_density_km2 =auto |timezone = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]] |utc_offset = +3:30 |timezone_DST = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]] |utc_offset_DST = +4:30 |coordinates = {{coord|29|13|59|N|56|36|08|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = 2280 |website = |area_code = 0347422 |footnotes = }} '''Baft''' ({{lang-fa|بافت}}, also [[romanize]]d as '''Bāft''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3054465}}</ref> is a city and capital of [[Baft County]], [[Kerman Province]], [[Iran]]. Baft is located {{convert|155|km|mi}} southwest of [[Kerman]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 35,008, in 8,265 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|08}}</ref> Notably, Baft is one of the highest cities in Iran{{according to whom|date=February 2017}}, at an elevation of about {{convert|2267|m|ft}}.<ref>[http://elevationmap.net/kerman-province-baft-iran?latlngs=(29.233038,56.60089719999996)]</ref>
==Khabr National Park==
Baft is one of the natural area in Iran. Within its local is the Khabr National Park which has been submitted by Iran as a [[World Heritage Site|UNESCO world heritage site]].<ref>UNESCO World Heritage Centre (2007) Khabr National Park and Ruchun Wildlife Refuge, web page, online at https://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/5219/, visited 2015-03-28</ref> Khabr National Park has a rich flora (about 750 species) and about 120 endemic species.
